summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on the UN operation in Cyprus, 
and urging parties to address the issue of missing persons urgently,
Noting the Government of Cyprus's agreement to extend the UN Peacekeeping 
Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) due to the prevailing conditions,
Welcoming UN efforts to prevent and control HIV/AIDS and other diseases,

1. Reaffirms its relevant Cyprus resolutions, particularly 1251 (1999) and 1283 (1999);
2. Extends UNFICYP's mandate until 15 December 2000;
3. Requests a report by 1 December 2000 on the implementation of this resolution;
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
